    "analysis": "Executor found widespread anomalies: multiple services' 'socket' KPIs (catalogue, catalogue-db, payment, queue-master, rabbitmq, session-db, user, user-db, rabbitmq-exporter) have all 25 in-window points >= global P95, with earliest anomaly at 2024-01-19 05:37:00 UTC. Many other KPIs are zero-baseline and likely false positives. Traces and detailed error_logs are empty, so we must rely on metrics and log.csv. To decide whether the socket anomalies represent real sustained faults (consecutive sub-series) or are artifacts of constant series/P95 equal to observed values, we need per-component-KPI time-series summaries within the incident window: counts, min/max, unique value counts, first/last values and timestamps. This will let us identify true faults (consecutive deviations) and their start times for root-cause localization. Next step: extract compact per-component-KPI statistics and limited unique-value lists for the socket KPIs (and rabbitmq-exporter mem) within the incident window.",
